<statement>
<p>For the following sequence, state the next three terms.</p>
<p>8, 12, 16, 20, <fillin characters="3" />, <fillin characters="3" />, <fillin characters="3" /></p>
<p>State a formula for the nth term: <fillin characters="6" />
</p>
<p>What type of sequence is this? </p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><p>arithmetic (linear)</p></li> 
<li><p>quadratic</p></li> 
<li><p>geometric (exponential)</p></li> 
<li><p>other</p></li> 
</ul></p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><p>24</p></li><li><p>28</p></li><li><p>32</p></li><li><p><m>\displaystyle{4}+{n}\cdot{4}</m></p></li><li><p>arithmetic (linear)</p></li></ul></p>
</solution>
